The Telegraph - Calcutta
 Monday, September 22, 2003 				 Hum Bhi Kuch Kam Nahin
																								Thanks to Anamika Kala Sangam, Hindi theatre buffs once again get a golden opportunity to watch a hilarious comedy that explores the relationship between couples, highlighting the different shades in their married-life. Madhav flirts with his wifes (Meera) best friend Radha. But Radhas husband discovers the extra-marital affair between his wife and her best friends husband and rushes to Meera with the news. But Meera handles the entire situation in such a tactful manner that it does not affect the lives of those concerned. The ever-popular Saas (mother-in-law) of Tu Tu Main Main fame, Reema Lagoo, who has several film and television hits to her credit, plays the lead in this Nath Theatre production, written by Shailesh Dave and directed by Kamlesh Mota. 																								When: Today at 7 pm																								Where: Kala Mandir
